{"title":"No. 6 Adventure Fork Gets Official with All the Features","link":"https://bikerumor.com/no-6-adventure-carbon-fork/","date":1736433505000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Adventure_1-1536x1025.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1025\" alt=\"No. 6 adventure carbon fork\" /></p>\n<p>Way back in 2022, No.6 was introduced by No. 22 as their in-house component brand. As stated by co-founder Bryce Gracey, “We created No. 6 as a sister brand to No. 22 because we could not find a fork on the market with the specifications we desired for our Titanium bikes. Our forks manage a wider tire clearance than other products while maintaining low weight and fantastic ride quality. All No. 6 Forks are now available for direct purchase in addition to our dedicated frame builder program.”</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Adventure_2-scaled.webp\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1025\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Adventure_2-1536x1025.webp\" alt=\"No. 6 adventure carbon fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Adventure_2-1536x1025.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Adventure_2-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Adventure_2-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Adventure_2-768x513.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Adventure_2-2048x1367.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Adventure_2-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Adventure_2-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, in addition to the Gravel, Road Disc, and Road Rim brake carbon forks, No. 6 is getting an Adventure model added to the lineup. Like their past forks, the carbon Adventure fork was created to offer specs that were hard to find on existing forks coupled with a low 404g weight with an uncut steerer. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Along with the typical three-pack accessory mounts on the side of the fork legs, the fork offers full fender mounts, and internal routing for a dynamo system. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_3_4Vert.png\"><img width=\"1154\" height=\"2048\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_3_4Vert.png\" alt=\"No. 6 adventure carbon fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_3_4Vert.png 1154w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_3_4Vert-169x300.png 169w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_3_4Vert-68x120.png 68w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_3_4Vert-768x1363.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_3_4Vert-866x1536.png 866w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_FrontVert.png\"><img width=\"1154\" height=\"2048\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_FrontVert.png\" alt=\"No. 6 adventure carbon fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_FrontVert.png 1154w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_FrontVert-169x300.png 169w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_FrontVert-68x120.png 68w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_FrontVert-768x1363.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_FrontVert-866x1536.png 866w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Offered only with a 1 1/8 – 1 1/2″ tapered steerer, 50mm rake, and 398mm axle-to-crown, the fork offers 700c x 50mm tire clearance (with 5mm of clearance on either side of the tire) or 650b x 2.3″. Brake cable routing is either semi-internal entering at the top of the fork leg, or fully internal entering through the steerer. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Features</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Steerer tube length: 350mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cable routing: semi-internal entering at the top of the fork leg or fully internal entering at the steerer</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rake: 50mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Axle-to-crown: 398mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Axle diameter: 12mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Maximum tire clearance: 50mm x 700c (5mm clearance all sides), 2.3″ x 650b</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Steerer diameter: 1-⅛” to 1-½” tapered</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fender mounts: Yes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Accessory mounts: Yes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dynamo routing: Yes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Weight:  440g with uncut steerer</li>\n\n\n\n<li>MSRP: $525 USD</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_internal-scaled.webp\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"865\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_internal-1536x865.webp\" alt=\"No. 6 adventure carbon fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_internal-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_internal-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_internal-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_internal-768x433.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_internal-2048x1154.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_internal-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_external-scaled.webp\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"865\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_external-1536x865.webp\" alt=\"No. 6 adventure carbon fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_external-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_external-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_external-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_external-768x433.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_external-2048x1154.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Routing_external-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork3_4Matched.png\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"865\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork3_4Matched-1536x865.png\" alt=\"No. 6 adventure carbon fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork3_4Matched-1536x865.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork3_4Matched-297x167.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork3_4Matched-120x68.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork3_4Matched-768x432.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork3_4Matched-1200x675.png 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork3_4Matched.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_DetailPlate.png\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"865\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_DetailPlate-1536x865.png\" alt=\"No. 6 adventure carbon fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_DetailPlate-1536x865.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_DetailPlate-297x167.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_DetailPlate-120x68.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_DetailPlate-768x432.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_DetailPlate-1200x675.png 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/AdventureFork_DetailPlate.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikeru